				<category name="Rarity Color Fix">
					<comment>#NoMoreJebaited</comment>
					<comment>By Koby</comment>
					<comment>Image Album: https://imgur.com/a/AEZNy</comment>
					<comment>Changes the rarity color of unique aftermarket items to a dark teal to be more distinguishable from other items.</comment>
					<comment>Changes the color of Moxxi weapons to a blood red.</comment>
					<comment>Supports Gemstone weapons from the Unofficial Community Patch.</comment>
					<comment>Changes the order of items in the inventory: Pearl -> Seraph -> (Unique Uniques if enabled) -> Legendary -> Moxxi -> Unique -> Gemstone -> E-Tech -> Very Rare...</comment>
					<comment>Has an optional module to turn all Heads and Skins to a grey-ish color.</comment>
					<comment>Has an optional module to turn all Legendary items which don't world drop into Dark Orange items (Unique Uniques).</comment>
					<comment>Also changes the color of Moxxi weapons to a blood red.</comment>
					<comment>Has 2 money color options: Mint green money (default) and normal yellow.</comment>
					<comment>Full BLCMM support!</comment>
					<comment>Thanks to Dave for providing the Rarity Colors resource.</comment>
					<comment>Also thanks to FromDarkHell for writing me a script for the Heads and Skins.</comment>
					<comment>INCOMPATIBILITY NOTE:</comment>
					<comment>This mod will most likely conflict with any mod which changes rarity colors and rarities of items.</comment>
					<comment>If you have basic modding and reading knowledge, you can fix the rarity in the weapon/item mod yourself.</comment>
					<category name="Rarity Color Change (Pick your Money Color here)" MUT="true">
						<category name="Rarity Color Change (Yellow Money)">
							<code profiles="">set WillowGame.GlobalsDefinition RarityLevelColors 				<category name="Fix Sage and Orchid Endgame Chests">
					<comment>By Koby</comment>
					<comment>Fixes the red chests at the end of "Captain Scarlett and Her Pirate's Booty" and "Sir Hammerlocks Big Game Hunt" not being able to contain Pearlescent weapons.</comment>
					<comment>At some point, Gearbox replaced all "WEAPONTYPE_Legendary" loot pools with "WEAPONTYPE_LegendaryPlusPearl". They forgot for these chests. I fixed it.</comment>

				<category name="Less Salvador Scream">
					<comment>By soze (Mike)</comment>
					<comment>Makes Salvador scream less during Gunzerking.</comment>
					<category name="Code">
						<hotfix name="FatMidgetStopScream" level="None">
							<code profiles="">set GD_Mercenary_Skills.ActionSkill.ActionSkill_Gunzerking:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0.Behavior_PostAkEvent_52 Event None</code>
							<code profiles="">set GD_Mercenary_Skills.ActionSkill.ActionSkill_Gunzerking:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0.Behavior_PostAkEvent_53 Event None</code>
							<code profiles="">set GD_Mercenary_Skills.ActionSkill.ActionSkill_Gunzerking:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0.Behavior_PostAkEvent_54 Event None</code>
